arts.ttl: Colchester United drew with Tranmere Rovers in League Two
arts.sum: "My memories of Tranmere are of Friday night football when John Aldridge was manager and they had a really, really good team. He told BetVictor : "Colchester United vs Tranmere Rovers is interesting, we went to Colchester when I was at Stoke, the game before we got promoted, we had to play Leicester in the last game.

arts.ttl: Colchester United 1 Tranmere Rovers 1 - match report as Lisbie rescues U's point
arts.sum: Colchester boss Danny Cowley named new summer signings Ben Perry, Jack Tucker, Jaden Williams and Will Goodwin in his starting line-up, while Adrian Akande was on the bench following his arrival from Reading. Lisbie collected Jack Tucker's pass in the area before lifting an excellent shot into the top corner to score his first professional goal and earn the U's a point after they had trailed for much of the game to Connor Jennings' early goal.
